itemDescription: Winner of the British Beauty Contest

wikipedia_page.main: Dee-Ann Kentish-Rogers (born 13 January 1993) is a British-Anguillan politician, model, beauty pageant titleholder and former athlete who was crowned as Miss Universe Great Britain 2018 and represented Great Britain at the Miss Universe 2018 pageant. She placed in the Top 20 at the end of the pageant. Rogers became the first black woman to represent Great Britain at a Miss Universe pageant.

response: *Dee-Ann Kentish-Rogers, British-Anguillan Athlete, Barrister, Beauty Queen, Model and Politician who represented Antigua and Barbuda at the 2014 Commonwealth Games in the heptathlon event and was crowned Miss Universe Great Britain 2018 and placed Top 20 at Miss Universe 2018
In 2018, Dee-Ann Kentish-Rogers from Anguilla, a British Overseas Territory, won the crown. She is a past Commonwealth Games heptathlete and a barrister at law.

Valley South (Anguilla House of Assembly Constituency)
response: Valley South is a constituency of the Anguillan House of Assembly. The incumbent is Dee-Ann Kentish-Rogers of the Anguilla Progressive Movement.
